 Analyst Ratings For Basic Energy Services (NYSE:BAS)
Today, Credit Suisse Group AG initiated coverage on Basic Energy Services (NYSE:BAS) with a Neutral .
There are 9 hold ratings, 3 buy ratings on the stock.
The current consensus rating on Basic Energy Services (NYSE:BAS) is Hold (Score: 2.25) with a consensus target price of $20.13 per share, a potential 26.68% downside.
Some recent analyst ratings include

7/21/2017-Credit Suisse Group AG initiated coverage with a Neutral rating.
7/12/2017-Piper Jaffray Companies Reiterated Rating of Neutral.
6/21/2017-Seaport Global Securities was Downgraded by analysts at Seaport Global Securities from a “Buy ” rating to a ” Neutral” rating.
4/19/2017-Instinet Reiterated Rating of Buy.
4/19/2017-Nomura initiated coverage with a Buy rating.
3/29/2017-Deutsche Bank AG Reiterated Rating of Hold.
12/29/2016-Johnson Rice Upgrade from a “Hold ” rating to a ” Accumulate” rating.

