Credit Suisse Begins Coverage on Basic Energy Services, Inc. (BAS) Setting A Rating Of “Neutral” 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsCredit Suisse Begins Coverage on Basic Energy Services, Inc. (BAS) Setting A Rating Of “Neutral”
July 21, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Basic Energy Services, Inc. (NYSE:BAS). 
  On June 21, 2017 the stock rating was set at “Neutral” according to a Seaport Global report a cut from the previous “” rating. On November 10 the company was downgraded from “Buy” to “Hold” in an announcement from Deutsche Bank.
 On July 25 the stock rating was downgraded to “Sector Perform” from “” by analysts at Johnson Rice. On July 25 the company was changed to a “Sector Perform” by iBERIA Capital Partners which is down from the previous “Outperform” rating.        Advertisement






 July 11 investment analysts at Jefferies maintained a company rating of “Hold” but lowered the price target from $6.50 to $1.50.
 The company is trading down since yesterday’s close of $29.01.  Company chares are trading at $28.04 a tad above the 50 day moving average of $25.33 and a tad under the 200 day moving average of $32.10.  The 50 day moving average was up $2.71 or +10.71% and the 200 day average went down $-4.06 or -12.64%. 
 Basic Energy Services, Inc., launched on January 7, 2003, provides a range of well site services in the United States to oil and natural gas drilling and producing companies, including completion and remedial services, fluid services, well servicing and contract drilling. The Business’s segments include Completion and Remedial Services, Fluid Services, Well Servicing and Contract Drilling. The Business’s operations are managed regionally and are concentrated in the United States onshore oil and natural gas producing regions located in Texas, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Arkansas, Kansas, Louisiana, Wyoming, North Dakota, Colorado, Utah, Montana, West Virginia, California, Ohio and Pennsylvania. Its operations are focused on liquids-rich basins, as well as natural gas-focused shale plays characterized by prolific reserves. It has a presence in the Permian Basin and the Bakken, Eagle Ford, Haynesville and Marcellus shales.. 
 As of the last earnings report the EPS was $-2.07 and is projected to be $-1.85 for the current year with 25,999,000 shares presently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is estimated at $-0.28 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $0.60. 
