Basic Energy Services, Inc. (NYSE:BAS) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Basic Energy Services, Inc. (NYSE:BAS) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume
July 18, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Trading volume for Basic Energy Services, Inc. was 324K in the last trading session.  Volume was down 78.58% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in BAS.   As of the end of the quarter Citadel Advisors LLC had acquired 688,870 shares growing its position 4,028.5%. The value of the total investment in Basic Energy Services, Inc. went from $14,000 to $1,892,000 increasing 13,414.3% quarter over quarter. As of quarter end State Street Corp had bought  a total of 11,022 shares growing its holdings by 7.7%. The value of the investment in BAS decreased from $241,000 to $127,000 a change of 47.3% for the reporting period.
 As of quarter end Asset Planning Services, Ltd. had bought  a total of 116 shares growing its stake by 5.0%. The value of the investment in Basic Energy Services, Inc. increased from $2,000 to $4,000 a change of $2,000 quarter to quarter. As of quarter end Credit Suisse AG/ had disposed of 84,178 shares trimming its stake by 85.4%. The value of the company’s investment in Basic Energy Services, Inc. went from $166,000 to $12,000 a change of $154,000 since the last quarter.
  On June 21 the company was rated “Neutral” according to a Seaport Global report which is down from the previous “” rating. On November 10 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a report from Deutsche Bank.
 On July 25, 2016 the stock rating was changed to a “Sector Perform” by Johnson Rice which was a cut from the previous “” rating. On July 25 the company was downgraded from “Outperform” to “Sector Perform” by analysts at iBERIA Capital Partners.





 July 11 investment analysts at Jefferies kept the company rating at “Hold” but moved down the price target  to $1.50 from $6.50. On April 22 the stock rating was upgraded to “Market Perform” from “Underperform” in a report issued by Raymond James.
 The company is now unchanged since yesterday’s close of $28.55.  Shares of the company are trading at $28.55 a bit higher than $25.91, the 50 day moving average and a tad under the 200 day moving average of $32.78.  The 50 day moving average moved up $2.64 whereas the 200 day average was down by -12.91%. 
 As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $-2.07 and is projected to be $-1.85 for the current year with 25,999,000 shares now outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS will be $-0.28 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $0.70. 
 Basic Energy Services, Inc., launched on January 7, 2003, provides a range of well site services in the United States to oil and natural gas drilling and producing companies, including completion and remedial services, fluid services, well servicing and contract drilling. The Business’s segments include Completion and Remedial Services, Fluid Services, Well Servicing and Contract Drilling. The Business’s operations are managed regionally and are concentrated in the United States onshore oil and natural gas producing regions located in Texas, New Mexico, Oklahoma, Arkansas, Kansas, Louisiana, Wyoming, North Dakota, Colorado, Utah, Montana, West Virginia, California, Ohio and Pennsylvania. Its operations are focused on liquids-rich basins, as well as natural gas-focused shale plays characterized by prolific reserves. It has a presence in the Permian Basin and the Bakken, Eagle Ford, Haynesville and Marcellus shales..






